import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]
    data['budgetYear'] = data['budgetYear'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of budget values over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Budget Value Trend'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    data['forecastYear'] = data['forecastYear'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='forecastYear', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecastYear values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

    return plt;

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='value', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['value'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['value'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Budget Value')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budget values?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
